![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

In `mapPrismaError`, unhandled errors that are instances of `Error` are returned as-is. This can lead to inconsistent error shapes on the client-side and potentially leak sensitive information if the server framework serializes the full error object in development. It's better to wrap all unhandled errors in a `ServerFnError` to ensure a consistent error contract.

```typescript
  if (error instanceof Error) {
    return new ServerFnError('INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR', { message: error.message });
  }

  return new ServerFnError('INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR', {
    message: 'Unhandled error',
  });
```

_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Handle `CONFLICT` target when backend returns a string value.**

Right now only array-form targets are checked. If `error.data.target` is `'title'` (string), the title field error won’t be set and users get a generic toast instead.



<details>
<summary>Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
     onError: (error) => {
+      const isTitleConflict =
+        error.data?.target === 'title' ||
+        (Array.isArray(error.data?.target) &&
+          error.data.target.includes('title'));
+
       if (
         isServerFnError(error) &&
         error.code === 'CONFLICT' &&
-        Array.isArray(error.data?.target) &&
-        error.data.target.includes('title')
+        isTitleConflict
       ) {
         form.setError('title', {
           message: t('book:manager.form.titleAlreadyExist'),
         });
         return;
       }
```
</details>

