**Keep raw session tokens off the client.**

`getUserSessions` currently returns full session rows, which includes `token`, and `revokeUserSession` then asks the browser to send that token back. That exposes session/revocation credentials to any client with `session:list` access. Return a non-secret session identifier from the list endpoint and resolve/validate the token server-side before revoking.



<details>
<summary>Suggested direction</summary>

```diff
 export const zRevokeUserSessionInput = () =>
-  z.object({ id: z.string(), sessionToken: z.string() });
+  z.object({ id: z.string(), sessionId: z.string() });
```

