_🧹 Nitpick_ | _🔵 Trivial_ | _💤 Low value_

**Server-Timing header not emitted on error paths.**

The `finalize` function (which sets the `Server-Timing` header) is only called on the success path (line 191). When an error is thrown, the timing data collected during the request is lost. Consider calling `finalize` in a `finally` block if observability on error paths is valuable.



<details>
<summary>♻️ Proposed change to emit timings on all paths</summary>

```diff
 export async function withPublicContext<T>(
   fn: (ctx: PublicContext) => Promise<T>
 ): Promise<T> {
   const start = performance.now();
   const { session, procedureLogger, timings } = await buildContext();
   procedureLogger.info('Before');

   return await timingStore.run({ prisma: [] }, async () => {
     try {
       const ctx: PublicContext = {
         user: session?.user ?? null,
         session: session?.session ?? null,
         db,
         logger: procedureLogger,
       };
       const result = await fn(ctx);
-      finalize(procedureLogger, timings, start);
       return result;
     } catch (error) {
       throw handleError(error, procedureLogger);
+    } finally {
+      finalize(procedureLogger, timings, start);
     }
   });
 }
```
</details>

